
You said:
is there a discord bot I can use to warn users of ban if they continue to ping a specific user

ChatGPT said:
Yes ‚Äî there are Discord bots that can warn (and even auto-punish) users who repeatedly ping a specific user or role.
üîê What You‚Äôre Looking For
You want a bot that can:
Detect when someone mentions/pings a specific user or role
Send a warning
Optionally take action (mute, temp-ban, kick) if the behavior continues
üõ† Discord Bots That Can Do This
1. Dyno
Powerful moderation module
Can trigger automated response or punishment when a rule is broken
You can configure a custom automod rule like:
‚û§ If user mentions <@User> more than X times ‚Üí warn/mute/kick
Works well for per-user or per-role monitoring
üëâ Free with generous features; paid for advanced logs/statistics
2. MEE6
Custom automoderation available
You can set a word/phrase blacklist
For example:
@SpecificUser ‚Üí trigger a warning
Also supports auto-mute or auto-kick after repeated offenses
‚ö†Ô∏è Limitation: Basic custom automod like this might require MEE6 Premium depending on complexity
3. Carl-bot
Excellent for automod and complex triggers
You can set an automod rule to detect user/role mentions
‚û§ When a specified user is mentioned too many times ‚Üí issue warning, mute, etc.
Very granular settings
üí° Particularly good if you want customizable response messages
4. Tatsu / Arcane / YAGPDB
These can also do automod to detect mentions, but require:
Enabling custom automod or regex filters
More advanced setup than Dyno or Carl-bot
üß† How This Usually Works
Most bots let you configure automoderation (automod) with rules such as:
Condition	Action
Mentioning User X more than N times	Send a warning message
Mentioning after warning	Mute for X minutes
Repeat offense	Kick/Ban
You can usually customize:
The trigger (which user/role)
Threshold (how many pings)
First action (warning or delete message)
Escalation (mute ‚Üí kick ‚Üí ban)
üîß Example Setup (Carl-bot)
Invite Carl-bot to your server
Enable automod
Create filter:
Trigger: mention of @UserToProtect
Actions:
‚Ä¢ Warn
‚Ä¢ (Optional) Mute on further mentions
Adjust punishments & cooldowns
üöÄ If You Want a Custom Bot
If none of the existing bots fit exactly what you want, you can also:
Write a custom Discord bot with Discord.js or PyCord
Listen for messageCreate events
Check if message.mentions.users includes the protected user
Track counts per user and escalate warnings
I can help with a small code snippet if you want!
