You said:
I want it to warn of ban if it is a specific user who continues to ping another important user

ChatGPT said:
Got it ‚Äî you want a Discord bot that watches for a specific user repeatedly pinging another specific (important) user and warns them that they‚Äôll be banned if they continue.
Here are the best ways to do that:

‚úÖ Option 1 ‚Äî Use an Existing Bot (No Coding)
üîπ Carl-bot (Good Choice)
You can set up an automod rule to watch for mentions of the important user but only trigger warnings if the mention comes from one specific user.
‚ö†Ô∏è Built-in automod usually doesn‚Äôt filter by sender user AND mention target at once ‚Äî but Carl-bot‚Äôs custom automod + tags can be scripted to approximate it.

‚úÖ Option 2 ‚Äî Make a Custom Bot (Most Control)
If you want it precise (only warn if UserA pings UserB repeatedly), then a small custom Discord bot is the best and most reliable way. Here‚Äôs what it would do:
‚úî Track messages
‚úî If the sender is SpecificUserA and they mention ImportantUserB, then:

First time ‚Üí send a warning message
If repeated ‚Üí send stricter warning
If still continued ‚Üí kicks/bans the user
üìå Example Bot Logic (Discord.js)
Here‚Äôs a ready-to-use example in Node.js (Discord.js):
const {Client, GatewayIntentBits, PermissionsBitField} = require("discord.js");
const client = new Client({ intents: [
  GatewayIntentBits.Guilds,
  GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages,
  GatewayIntentBits.MessageContent
]});

// Replace these with real IDs:
const WATCHED_USER = "ID_OF_USER_WHO_MIGHT_PING";
const PROTECTED_USER = "ID_OF_IMPORTANT_USER";

let warnCount = 0;

client.on("messageCreate", async (message) => {
  if (message.author.id !== WATCHED_USER) return; // Only watch this user
  if (!message.mentions.users.has(PROTECTED_USER)) return; // Must mention the protected user

  warnCount++;

  if (warnCount === 1) {
    message.reply("‚ö†Ô∏è Please stop pinging that user ‚Äî continued pings may get you banned.");
  } else if (warnCount === 2) {
    message.reply("‚ùó This is your final warning. Stop pinging or you *will* be banned.");
  } else {
    const member = message.guild.members.cache.get(WATCHED_USER);
    if (member?.bannable) {
      await member.ban({ reason: "Repeatedly pinging protected user after warnings" });
      message.channel.send("‚úÖ User has been banned due to continued pings.");
    }
  }
});

client.login("YOUR_BOT_TOKEN");
‚û°Ô∏è What it does:
Only reacts if WATCHED_USER pings PROTECTED_USER
First time ‚Üí warning
Second time ‚Üí final warning
Third time ‚Üí ban
üõ† How to Set This Up
Step 1 ‚Äî Create a Discord Bot
Go to the Discord Developer Portal
Create a new application ‚Üí add a bot
Give the bot these privileges:
‚úÖ Read messages
‚úÖ Send messages
‚úÖ Ban members (if you want auto-ban)
Generate the bot token and paste it into the client.login(...).
Step 2 ‚Äî Invite the Bot to Your Server
Use a URL like:
https://discord.com/oauth2/authorize?client_id=YOUR_CLIENT_ID&scope=bot&permissions=8
Permissions 8 = Administrator (for banning) ‚Äî or adjust to the least privileges needed.
Step 3 ‚Äî Run the Bot
Install dependencies and run:
npm install discord.js
node bot.js
‚ùì Customizations You Can Add
‚úî Reset warning count after some time
‚úî Log warnings in a dedicated channel
‚úî DM the user warnings instead of public replies
‚úî Add configurable thresholds
If You Want It Without Coding
I can help you configure Carl-bot / Dyno / MEE6 rules ‚Äî just tell me:
The Discord IDs of the pinger and the protected user
Whether you want temporary mutes or bans after warnings
I‚Äôll write exact setup steps!

