ChatGPT said:
Since you can develop the bot, deployment is mainly about where it runs 24/7 and how you manage the process.
Here are the most common (and practical) deployment options for a Discord bot:

ü•á Option 1 ‚Äî Deploy to a VPS (Most Reliable)
This is the most stable method.
Popular VPS Providers
DigitalOcean
Vultr
Linode
Hetzner
üí∞ Cost: ~$4‚Äì6/month
‚úÖ Best for long-term bots
‚úÖ Full control
‚úÖ Always online
How to Deploy on a VPS (Node.js Example)
1Ô∏è‚É£ Create a VPS (Ubuntu 22.04 recommended)
2Ô∏è‚É£ SSH into it
ssh root@your_server_ip
3Ô∏è‚É£ Install Node.js
curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | sudo -E bash -
sudo apt install nodejs -y
Check:
node -v
npm -v
4Ô∏è‚É£ Upload Your Bot
Either:
Use Git:
git clone your_repo_url
Or:
Upload files via SFTP (FileZilla, etc.)
Then:
cd your_bot_folder
npm install
5Ô∏è‚É£ Add a Process Manager (IMPORTANT)
Install PM2:
npm install -g pm2
Start your bot:
pm2 start bot.js --name "discord-bot"
Make it auto-start on reboot:
pm2 startup
pm2 save
Now your bot:
Restarts if it crashes
Starts automatically on server reboot
Runs 24/7
ü•à Option 2 ‚Äî Railway (Easiest Cloud Deploy)
Railway
‚úÖ Very beginner-friendly
‚úÖ GitHub auto-deploy
‚ùå Limited free tier

Steps:

Push bot to GitHub
Create Railway project
Connect GitHub repo
Add DISCORD_TOKEN as an environment variable
Deploy
That‚Äôs it.
ü•â Option 3 ‚Äî Render
Render
Similar to Railway.

Free tier exists but:

Sleeps after inactivity
May delay bot reconnects
üñ• Option 4 ‚Äî Run It on Your Own PC
You can, but:
‚ùå Bot goes offline if PC turns off
‚ùå Not ideal long-term
‚ùå IP changes can cause issues

Good for testing only.

üîê Important Deployment Tips
‚úÖ Use Environment Variables (Never Hardcode Token)
Instead of:
client.login("YOUR_TOKEN")
Use:
client.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN)
Then set on server:
export DISCORD_TOKEN=your_real_token
Or use a .env file with:
DISCORD_TOKEN=your_real_token
‚úÖ Make Sure Bot Has Proper Privileges
In the Discord Developer Portal:
Enable Privileged Gateway Intents if needed:
Message Content Intent
Members Intent
And ensure:
Bot role is above users it may ban
It has "Ban Members" permission
üí° For Your Use Case (Specific User Ping Watcher)
Your bot:
Doesn‚Äôt need a database unless you want persistent warning tracking
Can run very lightweight
VPS $4/month is more than enough
üî• What I Recommend For You
If:
This is a small server ‚Üí Railway is fastest
You want something stable & permanent ‚Üí $5 VPS + PM2
You want zero monthly cost ‚Üí run locally (not ideal)
If you'd like, tell me:
Node.js or Python?
Do you want persistent warning tracking?
Do you want logs?
