Step 1 ‚Äî Prepare Your Bot Code
Make sure your bot code (Node.js or Python) is ready.
For Node.js, your main file (e.g., bot.js) should use environment variables for your token:

const { Client, GatewayIntentBits } = require("discord.js");
const client = new Client({ intents: [GatewayIntentBits.Guilds, GatewayIntentBits.GuildMessages, GatewayIntentBits.MessageContent] });

const WATCHED_USER = "ID_OF_USER_WHO_MIGHT_PING"; // replace with the user ID
const PROTECTED_USER = "ID_OF_IMPORTANT_USER"; // replace with the important user ID

let warnCount = 0;

client.on("messageCreate", async (message) => {
  if (message.author.id !== WATCHED_USER) return;
  if (!message.mentions.users.has(PROTECTED_USER)) return;

  warnCount++;

  if (warnCount === 1) {
    message.reply("‚ö†Ô∏è Please stop pinging that user ‚Äî continued pings may get you banned.");
  } else if (warnCount === 2) {
    message.reply("‚ùó This is your final warning. Stop pinging or you *will* be banned.");
  } else {
    const member = message.guild.members.cache.get(WATCHED_USER);
    if (member?.bannable) {
      await member.ban({ reason: "Repeatedly pinging protected user after warnings" });
      message.channel.send("‚úÖ User has been banned due to continued pings.");
    }
  }
});

client.login(process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN);
Step 2 ‚Äî Create a Replit Project
Go to https://replit.com/ and sign up.
Click Create ‚Üí Choose Node.js (or Python if your bot is in Python).
Upload your bot files or copy your code into the repl.
Step 3 ‚Äî Set Your Discord Token
Click Secrets (üîí) in Replit (left sidebar).
Add a new secret:
Key: DISCORD_TOKEN
Value: Your bot token from Discord Developer Portal
Your bot code will now use process.env.DISCORD_TOKEN.
Step 4 ‚Äî Test Your Bot
Open the Shell in Replit
Run:
node bot.js
Check your server to see if the bot comes online.
If it works, stop it ‚Äî now we make it run 24/7.
Step 5 ‚Äî Make Your Bot Run 24/7 Using Uptime Robot
Free Replit instances sleep after ~1 hour. To prevent this:
Go to https://uptimerobot.com/ ‚Üí Sign up
Click Create New Monitor
Monitor Type: HTTP(s)
Friendly Name: Discord Bot
URL: Your Replit‚Äôs web server URL (see next step)
Interval: Every 5 minutes
Step 5a ‚Äî Add a Web Server to Your Bot
Replit only stays awake if the bot responds to HTTP requests. Add this to your bot.js:
const express = require("express");
const app = express();
const PORT = 3000;

app.get("/", (req, res) => res.send("Bot is alive!"));
app.listen(PORT, () => console.log(`Server running on port ${PORT}`));
Now Uptime Robot can ping https://your-repl-name.your-username.repl.co/ every 5 minutes to keep it alive.
Step 6 ‚Äî Run Your Bot in Replit
In Replit, click Run
Your bot will start and respond to messages
Uptime Robot keeps your bot awake 24/7
